Remo Stars have regained the top spot of the Nigeria Professional Football League(NPFL)  again after playing second fiddle to Rivers United and they are  still unbeaten team in the topflight at the end of the weekend games. The Sky Blue Stars pipped Shooting Stars 1-0 through Nduka Junior’s 62nd minute strike to occupy the first spot with 23 points from 11 games after Rivers United surrendered their unbeaten start to the season in Jos  after a 1-0 defeat to Plateau United. Jesse Akila’s 33rd minute strike was enough to keep Plateau United in third spot with 21 points while Rivers United are in the second position with 22 points.   Senegal win AFCON 2021     AFCON 2021: Mo Salah weeps as Egypt lose to Senegal     Ronaldo is first ever to reach 400m Instagram followers   Enyimba, meanwhile,  bagged their second away win of the season at Ijebu Ode yesterday to move to the fourth spot with 19 points as Victor Mbaoma’s 47th minute effort was enough to confine Sunshine Stars to their first home loss of the season. MFM held Akwa United to a goalless draw at the Teslim Balogun Stadium, Lagos while Tornadoes pipped Katsina United 2-1. Ahmadu Liman and Shamsudeen Hasim with the Ikon Allah Boys goals in the 20th and 24th minutes while Faisal Sani reduced the arrears fit the Changi Boys in the 42nd minute. - Advertisement - In Ilorin, Kwara United pipped Lobi Stars by a lone goal converted by Samad Kadiri in the 71st minute to move to the fifth spot with 18 points but the Pride of Benue slid to the 14th spot with 13 points. At the Tafawa Balewa Stadium, Bauchi, Enugu Rangers recovered from their home loss to Plateau United to secure a goalless draw against Wikki Tourists. They moved to the sixth spot with 17 points but the Giant Elephants are eighth on the log with 16 points.